Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Chapter 5  -  Section 5.2", "Title"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "I",
  StyleBox["n this ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" notebook, you will use ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontWeight->"Bold",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  StyleBox[" to find and compare Series solutions to a differential equation \
near an ordinary point. ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "\n\n",
  StyleBox["In most cases, to adapt this code to other problems, you will \
have to change only the input shown in red. To open a cell grouping, \
double-click on the right-hand side of the double cell marker.",
    FontSize->14]
}], "Subsubtitle"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
  "Problem 16:  (2 + ",
  Cell[BoxData[
      \(TraditionalForm\`x\^2\)]],
  ") y'' - x y' +  4y = 0\t\t"
}], "Section"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving the Differential Equation ", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We will begin by naming the left hand side of the differential equation \
and finding its Taylor series expansion about ",
  StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " = 0. This is done using the ",
  StyleBox["Series ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command in ",
  StyleBox["Mathematica",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  ". The numbers following the independent variable represent the number \
about which the series is expanded (0 in this case), followed by the number \
of terms you want in the expansion (5 in this case). After finding the \
series, we will insert the initial conditions. You may ignore warnings about \
spelling errors."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{\(Clear[x, y]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"lhs", "=", 
        StyleBox[\(\((2 + x\^2)\) \(y''\)[x]\  - \ x\ \(y'\)[x]\  + \ 
            4  y[x]\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"y0", "=", 
        StyleBox[\(-1\),
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";", " ", 
      RowBox[{"yp0", "=", 
        StyleBox["3",
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"lhsseries", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
        RowBox[{"lhs", ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"x", ",", 
              StyleBox["0",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
              StyleBox[",",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
              StyleBox["5",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], 
        "]"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(lhsseriesinit = 
      lhsseries /. {y[0] \[Rule] y0, \(y'\)[0] \[Rule] yp0}\)}], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "In this case, the right hand side of the equation is 0, but in order to \
determine the set of equations that will equate the coefficient of each power \
of ",
  StyleBox["x ",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  "to 0, we will need to create a series expansion for the right hand side. \
The ",
  StyleBox["LogicalExpand",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command here will set coefficients of like powers of ",
  StyleBox["x ",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  "equal to one another."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"rhs", "=", 
        StyleBox["0",
          FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"rhsseries", "=", 
        RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
          RowBox[{"rhs", ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"x", ",", 
                StyleBox["0",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[",",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox["5",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
      ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(setofeqs = 
      LogicalExpand[lhsseriesinit \[Equal] rhsseries]\)}], "Input"],

Cell["We will now solve this system of equations", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(solutionset = Solve[setofeqs]\)], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We can now write the series expansion for y and evaluate it at the initial \
conditions and at this solution set. The command ",
  StyleBox["Normal ",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  "truncates the series by removing the terms of higher order than we \
requested."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{"sery5", "=", 
      RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
        RowBox[{\(y[x]\), ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"x", ",", 
              StyleBox["0",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
              StyleBox[",",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
              StyleBox["5",
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], 
        "]"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(yapprox5 = \(Normal[
            sery5] /. {y[0] \[Rule] y0, \(y'\)[0] \[Rule] yp0}\) /. 
        solutionset[\([1]\)]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"sery4", "=", 
        RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
          RowBox[{\(y[x]\), ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              RowBox[{"x", ",", 
                StyleBox["0",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox[",",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], 
                StyleBox["4",
                  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
      ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(yapprox4 = \(Normal[
            sery4] /. {y[0] \[Rule] y0, \(y'\)[0] \[Rule] yp0}\) /. 
        solutionset[\([1]\)]\)}], "Input"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Analyzing the Solution Graphically", "Subsection"],

Cell["\<\
Now we can plot these two approximations. The four term approximation is \
green, while the five term is blue.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    RowBox[{"width", "=", 
      StyleBox["3",
        FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", \(pser = 
        Plot[{yapprox4, yapprox5}, {x, \(-width\), width}, 
          PlotStyle \[Rule] {RGBColor[0, 1, 0], 
              RGBColor[0, 0, 1]}];\)}], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "Something unusual seems to be happening outside of the interval from -1 to \
+1. What would happen if we use the ",
  StyleBox["N",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  StyleBox["DSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command?"
}], "Text"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Graphical Comparison to the Numerical Solution", "Subsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "We could try to look at the numerical solution to this differential \
equation using the ",
  StyleBox["NDSolve",
    FontWeight->"Bold"],
  " command"
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(numsoln1 = 
      NDSolve[{lhs \[Equal] rhs, y[0] \[Equal] y0, \(y'\)[0] \[Equal] yp0}, 
        y[x], {x, 0, width}]\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(numsoln2 = 
      NDSolve[{lhs \[Equal] rhs, y[0] \[Equal] y0, \(y'\)[0] \[Equal] yp0}, 
        y[x], {x, 0, \(-width\)}]\)}], "Input"],

Cell["\<\
This doesn't help much, since it cannot seem to get much past t=1.5  either. \
Let us explore the analytical solution arrived at earlier.\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[{
    \(\(numplot1 = 
        Plot[y[x] /. numsoln1, {x, 0, width}, 
          PlotStyle \[Rule] RGBColor[1, 0, 0]];\)\), "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    \(\(numplot2 = 
        Plot[y[x] /. numsoln2, {x, \(-width\), 0}, 
          PlotStyle \[Rule] RGBColor[1, 0, 0]];\)\)}], "Input"],

Cell[BoxData[
    \(\(Show[pser, numplot1, numplot2];\)\)], "Input"],

Cell[TextData[{
  "You can see that both of our approximations become less accurate as we \
move farther away from ",
  StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"],
  " = 0. We can try to narrow down the interval over which we plot these \
functions to see where the approximations seem reasonable."
}], "Text"],

Cell[BoxData[
    RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Show", "[", 
        RowBox[{"pser", ",", "numplot1", ",", "numplot2", ",", 
          RowBox[{"PlotRange", "\[Rule]", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
              StyleBox[\({\(-1.5\), 1.5}, {\(-4\), 4}\),
                FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]], "}"}]}], 
          ",", \(AspectRatio \[Rule] 1\)}], "]"}], ";"}]], "Input"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
